step.reason:
\text{If f(x) is not defined for some x, then how}\\
\text{can f'(x) be? That is why it is important to know}\\
\text{where all f(x) is defined before finding f'(x).}

step.tex:
\begin{align}
  \dfrac{d}{dx}\log(\log x) &= \dfrac{d}{d\log x}\log(\log x)
  \cdot\dfrac{d}{dx}\log x \\
  &= \dfrac{1}{\log x}\cdot\dfrac{1}{x} = \dfrac{1}{x\cdot\log x}, x\gt 1.
\end{align}
